The Governor of Oyo State, Seyi Makinde, has confirmed that ten new cases of coronavirus disease have been recorded in the state. Makinde who made the confirmation in a tweet via his Twitter account on Monday said eight cases were from iSON Xperiences. According to him, the state now has a total number of 292 confirmed cases of the viral infection. He said, ”COVID-19 update in Oyo State. ”The COVID-19 confirmation tests for ten suspected cases came back POSITIVE. ”Eight cases are from iSON Xperiences and the other two cases are from Ibadan North Local Government Area. ”So, the total number of confirmed cases in Oyo State is 292. Please call the Emergency Operations Centre on 08095394000 | 08095863000 | 08078288999 | 08078288800, if you have any COVID-19 symptoms: cough, fever, tiredness, body ache and shortness of breath. ” COVID-19: Oyo has 244 confirmed coronavirus cases - Makinde Oyo records 30 new cases of COVID-19 in 3 days Another 6 iSON staff test positive for coronavirus in Oyo